parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unwarranted airbag deployment can cause accidents, injuries, and vehicle damage, as well as unnecessary repair costs and emotional distress.
symptoms: often in low-speed or stationary situations

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can increase the risk of injury or fatality to occupants, as well as lead to more severe damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
even at moderate to high speeds

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving at high speeds or on slippery roads.
symptoms: Grinding or noise from the anti-lock brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving on hills or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: and the need for brake master cylinder service.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine head gasket can cause fluid leaks, engine misfires, and a loss of power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
A misfire on one or more cylinders can cause a loss of power, vibration, and decreased engine performance, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
A stuck valve can cause engine misfires, decreased engine performance, and a loss of power, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
